                <pb n="5008" facs="1e84e52835597bd4d2229709a02f0a93.jpg"/>
                <address>Zossen</address>
<date>Xmas Day 1915</date>
<salute>Dear old pet,</salute>
<p>No letter from you yet. I am so <lb/> lonely today - you remember last year <lb/> in 8 Hartstonge St. with the little ones running <lb/> wild &#x2014; why do you grip me so much <lb/> &amp; why are my thoughts so cluttered around <lb/> you? Mollie write me, I do so want your <lb/> sympathy, my work is so hard, and difficulties <lb/> so many - but of course if I had you here to <lb/> tell all my worries to, things would run <lb/> smoothly - I trust you and all at home <pb/>
           
                <pb n="5009" facs="b6ad122b71088b7eec53262038ffa443.jpg"/>
                are enjoying yourselves, even now as I write <lb/> this letter &#x2014;</p>
I cant write more now, fondest love <lb/> Kiss them all for me <lb/>
<salute> Yours ever <lb/>
<unclear>Cara</unclear></salute>
           
        </body>
    </text>
     

